history.content:
Yes, using the swap function means that once you get off the waitlist, you will drop your original class.

I don't think there is info as to what happens if you drop your language class; if you try it, do report back.

(My guess would either be: you lose your waitlist spot, or you keep your waitlist spot but it turns into a regular waitlist spot (and you won't be able to reenroll).)

children.subject: See above; I have not seen anyone in the last 19 days report on what happens when they do this.

Op here, I have dropped my class but remained on the waitlist, however still not off the waitlist, hopefully by adjustment period ill be able to enter some waitlisted classes. My spot didn't change when I dropped my enrolled class.

Can I drop B and remain on the waitlist for A?

history.content: Was really confused because during phase 1 I enrolled for 3 classes and then I tried to swap one of them (a language class) for cs c100(stats c100) and since the class was full it put me on a waitlist since then, and I'm still enrolled in my language class. Does this mean if I ever get off the waitlist, I would lose my language class enrollment and have to re-enroll? So now am I actually at 20 units of enrollment but if I get off the 100/160 waitlist I'd lose my enrollment in my other two classes? And if I were to drop and re-enroll say my language class right now would I get to keep my waitlist spot on cs c100 or does that disappear too? (None of them conflicts with each other)
